    <taskbody>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the <cmdname>Save</cmdname> toolbar button.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Acc063f9b-deec-43e4-88d0-02948f838c50/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_jjx_ps4_hx" align="center"/></cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Enter the title of the document, and click <cmdname>Save</cmdname>.</cmd>
                <info>Adding your initials to the beginning (e.g. MS) is a good way to indicate to
                    others that it is a file created by another CWRC-Writer tester. You may only
                    enter upper or lowercase letter; no numbers, spaces, or punctuation are
                        allowed.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A2967fccc-9027-4e4b-941b-cb947d50ead3/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_bpr_xd2_lp" align="center" scalefit="yes" scale="80"/></info>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Once you clicked on <cmdname>Save</cmdname>, the document validates and is successfully
                    saved.</cmd>
                <info>If the document is not valid, a pop-up will appear and you will be asked if
                    you would like to save anyway.<image placement="break"
                        href="http://beta.cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3Ad9900eb9-2f1b-424e-92a7-80835d54b5e3/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_grf_dbv_tp" align="center" scale="80" scalefit="yes"/>
